<br>
With the scenario Dwelfin explained, there's not any substantive difference between a warrior tanking and a knight barring defensive.   You see, when a druid is primary healer, there's no real &quot;warrior hitpoint/ac advantage&quot; if a Paladin has all his spells.    It evens out because the Paladin has buffs that stack with Pot9, which cut out the &quot;warrior HP/AC advantage&quot; to pretty much nil.<br>
<br>
If a Shaman is doing the primary healing (for instance when duoing with the Shaman) the same, equally equipped Paladin actually has a hitpoint/AC ADVANTAGE over the warrior.   In other words, he's a better tank from a melee defense perspective, which is supposedly the warrior's &quot;balancing&quot; point, while retaining the huge aggro advantage.<br>
<br>
