After reading this, the first picture that popped into my mind was a Terrorist on a camel launching 4 TOW missles at US M1A1 tanks followed by a stray Kuwaiti foot soldier sniping the Terrorist and then the CNN broadcast following the incident and saying &quot;Clearly we see here that the armed forces of Kuwait are far superior to anything the United States may have to offer.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ok, on a serious note though I still can't believe all the lower level people and non-warrior classes that are tearing into the guys that tank in elemental planes at level 65 with dozens and dozens of AA's.<br>
<br>
I mean I could understand if they just bought that account off playerauctions and obviously have no clue - but come on - they speak intelligently about their class and give specific situations as backup to their theories about taunt and agro.<br>
<br>
It's like this thread was started by a small businessman asking for tips on how to win over the biggest share of software sales in his local area... then Bill Gates posts telling him it's not as hard as it looks if you just do this, and this, and this... all from his own personal experiences.  Then some other small businessman down on his luck comes and starts bitching at Bill because he &quot;doesn't know what it's like down in the trenches working his way up&quot; or something.  I mean come on... Bill Gates wasn't born a billionaire, he had to work his way up and now he can share his secrets of success with other would be businessmen.<br>
<br>
Similarly (although on a far less grandeurous scale) we have folks here that are on both sides of the fence but nonetheless have IN GAME experiences far beyond our own.  They are trying to share their knowledge and experiences and are being shot down and poked fun at.  I know I would rather listen to the Bill Gates's of EQ than the folks who are still in my situation or even perhaps a bit lower on the totem poll of exp and AA's.<br>
<br>
Speaking from the point of view of someone that has come from level 61 to level 64 since he started posting here - I will say this... I do notice a VERY large increase in the reliability of taunt.  Do I have tangible hard copies of all the evidence ?  No.  I do however notice the compliments I am paid in group for my agro control and I do notice that folks remember me even though I'm just another Ogre War... nothing special about me really.<br>
<br>
I'm not concerned about statistics and theories or percentages or how things &quot;feel&quot;.  All I want is info and suggestions that will help me in actual in game situations.  While I have supplied example situations for argumental purposes to see the responses I did not want to see all the flame-fests and what not.  There is a great deal of info and knowledge to be gained from all these posts but anything of a flamatory nature that is not stated in a joking manner is very difficult to drudge/skim through in order to reach the helpful information.<br>
<br>
All in all a great thread and I hope it continues <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
~Ninaor<br>
<br>
p.s.  There was a mention earlier of a warrior that tanked an Ent and the druid was OOM at the end of the fight due to the fact that the Ent was unslowed.  Also, there was a comment that the druid heals negated the HP advantage of the warrior.  This is true.  However, where was the mention that the 1.5% less damage the warrior took would have caused the druid to be able to keep him alive where a knight would have been dead.  Also, where is the mention that the warrior did more damage to the Ent which also reduced the time it took to bring the mob down, and again, further added to the security of the situation.  I know it's not a full group exp grind situation, just another one of those situations that makes the WARRIOR stand out in the minds of the non-warrior classes that call the shots on who will replace the main tank.  This is becoming less and less about pure exp grouping efficiency and more and more about warrior image overall.  You don't have to impress the exp bean counters to get the groups every time - most times you just have to stand out in the crowd - being an ogre I tend to do that easily <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
