<br>
Over the course of  a year/year and a half or so there have been a vast number of changes in abilities/skills and the relative balance between classes. Stun, slow and heal aggro all have been tweaked and changed. For this reason it's hard to be sure that someones old experiences are totally accurate to the current situation. Also anyone who has advanced significantly into the elemental planes will be in an Uber guild - in all likelyhood that means those warriors were already 60 with a fair proportion of AA's and likely in SSra/VT gear when POP arrived. Geared to that level I wouldn't be at all surprised if their experiences are slightly different to those of us just now working our way up.<br>
<br>
I'm for once in agreement with Graal. The 1.5% difference in avoidance would have had little to no impact on that ent fight and very little visible difference in normal exp grouping. My disagreement with him is that (as stated above) in such an exp. situation I do not see defensive as an advantage of such magnitude that it truely warrants grouping a warrior over a knight (given the security knight aggro control brings to a fight). The long tradition of 'only a warrior will do' continues to colour peoples perceptions, unfortunately if (as I and others believe) that perception no longer has a solid basis, eventually people will twig to it (and are if you give credence to the threads on other boards). Therefore it's best to bring the subject up for debate before warriors truely lose their credibility....<br>
