<br>
Paladins and Shadowknights can heal themselves enough to supplement the 1.5% avoidance advantage held by warriors in that group. So, there goes the 1.5% theory. The damage aspect; the warrior himself deals more damage than an SK  (non-casting) or paladin. A shadowknight casting offensive spells can easily par or outdamage warriors. Furthermore, both the paladin and shadowknight can keep agro glued onto them, allowing other classes in the group to do more damage (wizards/mages wouldn't have to hold back on nukes for fear of getting too much agro, rogues wouldn't have to evade or stop attacking, monks wouldn't have to FD off or stop attacking, etc.) The warrior on his own will deal more damage, but a Knight will allow the group do deal more damage because the fear of getting agro isn't there. This scenario is FAR from one where warriors stand out.<br>
<br>
