Assuming warrior hp = knight hp + 750 <br>
<br>
Tanking with a druid healer - Warrior will have p/botn (618hp). Paladin will have symbol of marzin, heroic bond, aura of the crusader (1467hp). Paladin will now have 99 hp more then warrior.<br>
<br>
However, this is a moot point. A druid will heal 5075 on a crit NI with marrs gift and all Healing aa's. <br>
<br>
As long as this does not heal the tank to full, it will take the same damage to reduce the tank to where another heal is needed. After the first heal, the hp difference is completly void.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tanking with a Shaman Healer - Paladin will have a 717 hp advantage over a warrior.<br>
<br>
However this means nothing, as long as the max hp of the tank is greater then the amount of damage the shaman can heal constantly (better healing coverage then CH given canni).  In addition, the shaman cannot use torpor/quies on the paladin tank, lowering the average/tick he can heal. <br>
<br>
<br>
The only time hp makes a difference is with a cleric, in which the warrior would have a 408 hp advantage.<br>
<br>
<br>
